  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DFID Syria Independent Monitoring (SIM) Contract II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The UK Department for International Development (DFID) has been managing a complex and high-risk independent monitoring contract in Syria since 2016. DFID is seeking a supplier to undertake independent monitoring from March 2020. The contract is expected to run for three years (up to March 2023). It will deliver against five core outputs, including field monitoring visits to DFID-funded projects in Syria. It is intended to give DFID greater assurance of results being achieved by implementing partners, increase accountability to project beneficiaries and reduce the risk of aid diversion and fraud. It will also gather evidence that will help DFID and our implementing partners improve project design and enhance DFID&#x2019;s due diligence.</narrative>
  </description>
